#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:169 index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "Syntax"
msgstr "Sintaxe"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:170
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kalgebra; uses an intuitive algebraic syntax for entering user "
#| "functions, similar to that used on most modern graphing calculators. This "
#| "section lists the fundamental built-in operators available in &kalgebra;. "
#| "The author of &kalgebra; modeled this syntax after <ulink url=\"http://"
#| "maxima.sourceforge.net/\">Maxima</ulink> and <ulink url=\"http://www."
#| "maplesoft.com/products/maple/\">maple</ulink> for users that may be "
#| "familiar with these programs."
msgid ""
"&kalgebra; uses an intuitive algebraic syntax for entering user functions, "
"similar to that used on most modern graphing calculators. This section lists "
"the fundamental built-in operators available in &kalgebra;. The author of "
"&kalgebra; modeled this syntax after <ulink url=\"http://maxima.sourceforge."
"net/\">Maxima</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://www.maplesoft.com/products/"
"maple/\">Maple</ulink> for users that may be familiar with these programs."
msgstr ""
"&kalgebra; emprega unha sintaxe alxébrica intuitiva para inserir funcións "
"similar á empregada na maioría das calculadoras gráficas modernas. Esta "
"sección enumera os operadores incorporados fundamentais dispoñíbeis en "
"&kalgebra;. O autor de &kalgebra; modelou esta sintaxe baseándose en <ulink "
"url=\"http://maxima.sourceforge.net/\">Maxima</ulink> e <ulink url=\"http://"
"www.maplesoft.com/products/maple/\">maple</ulink> para usuarios que puidesen "
"estaren familiarizados con estes programas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:180
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "For users that are interested in the inner workings of &kalgebra;, user "
#| "entered expressions are converted to MathML on the backend. A rudimentary "
#| "understanding of the capabilities supported by MathML will go a long way "
#| "toward revealing the inner capabilities of &kalgebra;."
msgid ""
"For users that are interested in the inner workings of &kalgebra;, user "
"entered expressions are converted to &MathML; on the backend. A rudimentary "
"understanding of the capabilities supported by &MathML; will go a long way "
"toward revealing the inner capabilities of &kalgebra;."
msgstr ""
"Para quen se interese no funcionamento interno de &kalgebra;, as expresións "
"inseridas convértense en MathML na infraestrutura. A comprensión "
"rudimentaria das capacidades que permite MathML axudará moito a revelar as "
"capacidades internas de &kalgebra;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:187
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a list of the available operators we have by now:"
msgstr "Velaí unha lista dos operadores dispoñíbeis de momento:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:189
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "+ - * / : Addition, subtraction, multiplication and division."
msgid ""
"<literal>+ - * / </literal>: Addition, subtraction, multiplication and "
"division."
msgstr "+ - * / : Suma, resta, multiplicación e división."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:191
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "^, **: Power, you can use them both. Also it is possible to use the "
#| "unicode ² characters. Powers are one way to make roots too, you can do it "
#| "like: a**(1/b)"
msgid ""
"<literal>^, ** </literal>: Power, you can use them both. Also it is possible "
"to use the unicode <literal>²</literal> characters. Powers are one way to "
"make roots too, you can do it like: <literal>a**(1/b)</literal>"
msgstr ""
"^, **: Potencias; pódense empregar os dous. Tamén é posíbel empregar os "
"caracteres unicode ² . As potencias son tamén unha maneira de facer raíces; "
"pódense facer así: a**(1/b)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:194
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "-&gt; : lambda. It is the way to specify one or more free variables that "
#| "will be bound in a function. For example, in the expression, "
#| "<userinput>length:=(x,y)->(x*x+y*y)^0.5</userinput>, the lambda operator "
#| "is used to denote that x and y will be bound when the length function is "
#| "used."
msgid ""
"<literal>-&gt; </literal>: lambda. It is the way to specify one or more free "
"variables that will be bound in a function. For example, in the expression, "
"<userinput>length:=(x,y)->(x*x+y*y)^0.5</userinput>, the lambda operator is "
"used to denote that <literal>x</literal> and <literal>y</literal> will be "
"bound when the length function is used."
msgstr ""
"&gt;: lambda. É como se especifican unha ou máis variábeis libres limitadas "
"nunha función. Por exemplo, na expresión <userinput>length:=(x,y)->(x*x"
"+y*y)^0.5</userinput>, o operador lambda emprégase para denotar que x e y "
"están limitados cando se emprega a función length."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:199
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "x=a..b : This is used when we need to delimit a range (bounded variable"
#| "+uplimit+downlimit). This means that x goes from a to b."
msgid ""
"<literal>x=a..b </literal>: This is used when we need to delimit a range "
"(bounded variable+uplimit+downlimit). This means that <literal>x</literal> "
"goes from <literal>a</literal> to <literal>b</literal>."
msgstr ""
"x=a..b : Isto emprégase cando hai que delimitar un intervalo (variábel ligada"
"+límite superior+límite inferior). Isto significa que x vai de a a b."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:202
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "() : It is used to specify a higher priority."
msgid "<literal>() </literal>: It is used to specify a higher priority."
msgstr "() : Emprégase para especificar unha prioridade maior."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:203
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "abc(params) : Functions. When the parser finds a function, it checks if "
#| "abc is an operator. If it is, it will be treated as an operator, if it is "
#| "not, it will be treated as a user function."
msgid ""
"<literal>abc(params) </literal>: Functions. When the parser finds a "
"function, it checks if <literal>abc</literal> is an operator. If it is, it "
"will be treated as an operator, if it is not, it will be treated as a user "
"function."
msgstr ""
"abc(paráms) : Funcións. Cando o analizador atopa unha función, comproba se "
"abc é un operador. Se o é, trátase como operador; se non o é, trátase como "
"función do usuario."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:206
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| ":= : Definition. It is used to define a variable value. You can do things "
#| "like x:=3, x:=y being y defined or not or perimeter:=r->2*pi*r."
msgid ""
"<literal>:= </literal>: Definition. It is used to define a variable value. "
"You can do things like <userinput>x:=3</userinput>, <userinput>x:=y</"
"userinput> being <literal>y</literal> defined or not or <userinput>perimeter:"
"=r->2*pi*r</userinput>."
msgstr ""
":= : Definición. Emprégase para definir un valor variábel. Pódense facer "
"cousas como x:=3, x:=y, estando y definido ou non ou perímetro:=r->2*pi*r."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:210
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "? : Piecewise condition definition. Piecewise is the way we can define "
#| "conditional operations in &kalgebra;. Put another way, this is a way of "
#| "specifying an if, elseif, else condition. If we introduce the condition "
#| "before the '?' it will use this condition only if it is true, if it finds "
#| "a '?' without any condition, it will enter in the last instance. Example: "
#| "piecewise { x=0 ? 0, x=1 ? x+1, ? x**2 }"
msgid ""
"<literal>? </literal>: Piecewise condition definition. Piecewise is the way "
"we can define conditional operations in &kalgebra;. Put another way, this is "
"a way of specifying an if, elseif, else condition. If we introduce the "
"condition before the '<literal>?</literal>' it will use this condition only "
"if it is true, if it finds a '<literal>?</literal>' without any condition, "
"it will enter in the last instance. Example: <userinput>piecewise { x=0 ? 0, "
"x=1 ? x+1, ? x**2 }</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"? : Definición de condición de segmento. Segmento é como podemos definir as "
"operacións condicionais en &kalgebra;. Dito doutro xeito, é outra maneira de "
"especificar unha condición if, elseif ou else. Se se insire a condición "
"antes do «?», só emprega esta condición se é verdadeira; se atopa un «?» sen "
"ningunha condición, entra na última instancia. Exemplo: piecewise { x=0 ? 0, "
"x=1 ? x+1, ? x**2 }"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:217
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "{ } : MathML container. It can be used to define a container. Mainly "
#| "useful for working with piecewise."
msgid ""
"<literal>{ } </literal>: &MathML; container. It can be used to define a "
"container. Mainly useful for working with piecewise."
msgstr ""
"{} : Contedor de MathML. Pódese empregar para definir un contedor. É útil "
"especialmente para traballar con segmentos."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:220
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "= &gt; &gt;= &lt; &lt;= : Value comparators for equal, greater, greater "
#| "or equal, less and less or equal respectively"
msgid ""
"<literal>= &gt; &gt;= &lt; &lt;= </literal>: Value comparators for equal, "
"greater, greater or equal, less and less or equal respectively."
msgstr ""
"= &gt; &gt;= &lt; &lt;= : Comparadores de valor para igual que, maior que, "
"maior ou igual que, menor que e menor ou igual que, respectivamente"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:224
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Now you could ask me, why should the user mind about MathML? That’s easy. "
#| "With this, we can operate with functions like cos(), sin(), any other "
#| "trigonometrical functions, sum() or product(). It does not matter what "
#| "kind it is. We can use plus(), times() and everything which has its "
#| "operator. Boolean functions are implemented as well, so we can do "
#| "something like or(1,0,0,0,0)."
msgid ""
"Now you could ask me, why should the user mind about &MathML;? That’s easy. "
"With this, we can operate with functions like <function>cos()</function>, "
"<function>sin()</function>, any other trigonometrical functions, "
"<function>sum()</function> or <function>product()</function>. It does not "
"matter what kind it is. We can use <function>plus()</function>, "
"<function>times()</function> and everything which has its operator. Boolean "
"functions are implemented as well, so we can do something like "
"<function>or(1,0,0,0,0)</function>."
msgstr ""
"E agora poderíaseme preguntar que por que se debe preocupar o usuario por "
"MathML? É fácil. Con isto, podemos traballar con funcións como cos(), sin() "
"e outras funcións trigonométricas, sum() ou product(). Non importa de que "
"tipo sexan. Podemos empregar plus(), times() e todo o que teña un operador. "
"As funcións lóxicas tamén están incorporadas, polo que podemos facer cousas "
"como or(1,0,0,0,0)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:233
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "Using the Console"
msgid "Using the Calculator"
msgstr "Uso da consola"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:234
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kalgebra;'s console is useful as a calculator on steroids. The user may "
#| "enter expressions for evaluation in <guimenu>Calculate</guimenu> or "
#| "<guimenu>Evaluate</guimenu> mode, depending on the <guimenu>Console</"
#| "guimenu> menu selection."
msgid ""
"&kalgebra;'s calculator is useful as a calculator on steroids. The user may "
"enter expressions for evaluation in <guimenu>Calculate</guimenu> or "
"<guimenu>Evaluate</guimenu> mode, depending on the <guimenu>Calculator</"
"guimenu> menu selection."
msgstr ""
"A consola do &kalgebra; é útil como calculadora a fume de carozo. Pódense "
"introducir expresións para avaliar nos modos <guimenu>Calcular</guimenu> e "
"<guimenu>Avaliar</guimenu>, dependendo da selección do menú "
"<guimenu>Consola</guimenu>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:239
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In evaluation mode &kalgebra; simplifies the expression even if it sees an "
"undefined variable. When in calculation mode &kalgebra;, calculates "
"everything and if it finds an undefined variable shows an error."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
